        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 8:28PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 828 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Powderly, or 10 miles northeast of Paris, moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farmers Hill, Rufe, Millerton, Woodland, Redland, Wright City,
Kanawha, Holly Creek, Garvin, Manchester, Valliant, Kiomatia, and
Slim.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma...and northeastern Texas.</instruction>
